\begin{verbatim}
welch(input_signal, bs::Int, window = hanning(bs); fs::Int = 1,
      overlap = 0.5, scaling = :psd)
\end{verbatim}
Estimation of one-sided Autopower functions of a signal using the Welch method

\textbf{Inputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{input\_signal::Vector\{Real\}}: Input signal


\item \texttt{bs::Int}: Block size


\item \texttt{window}: Window function


\item \texttt{fs::Int}: Sampling rate


\item \texttt{overlap}: Overlap ratio between the segments


\item \texttt{scaling}: Scale of the PSD - see https://community.sw.siemens.com/s/article/the-autopower-function-demystified for more information

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{:psd} (default) - Power Spectral Density


\item \texttt{:esd} - Autopower Energy Spectral Density


\item \texttt{:spectrum} - Autopower spectrum


\item \texttt{:linear} - Autopower linear

\end{itemize}
\end{itemize}
\textbf{Outputs}

\begin{itemize}
\item \texttt{pxx}: Autopower


\item \texttt{freq}: Frequency range

\end{itemize}
